Package: pgaa
Type: Package
Title: Perturbation-response Generalized Association Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-06-06
Author: PGAA authors
Maintainer: First Author <author@institution.edu>
Description: A unified multi-statistic framework for analyzing single-cell
    perturbation screens (Perturb-seq). Provides S1 (1D Wasserstein distance)
    for distributional shifts, S2 (1D persistent homology) for bimodality shifts,
    and S3/S4 exploratory modules for dependency and count-model effects.
    All statistics share covariate residualization, within-cluster permutation
    nulls, and Storey pi0 calibration diagnostics.
